 In the Enterprise Access MS SQL Server gateway, the 
 hex function cannot return a dynamic length based on the 
 length of the input parameter.  Because of this limitation, 
 a hex_len parameter is provided to allow configuration of 
 the maximum number of input bytes the hex function will 
 process. The output length will be two times the size of 
 the input length.

 Default for hex_len is 30 bytes.  

